args:
Emile has built academies across Dyrenell, but
to what vile end? We follow our heroes on their
quest for answers to the very heart of the... Oh.
I'm being told the main campus is just across
the border. Lovely. We follow them there.
Heh heh heh... HAAA HA HA HA HA!
The Emile Academy opens its doors today!
Look alive, folks! We've got trouble!
What is it? Don't tell me we're under\nimperial siege again!
Siege, no; imperial shenanigans, yes.\nGet this: there's an Emile Academy!
Apparently, the little goon's gone and\nbuilt schools all across the Empire.
And now he's wranglin' a buncha kiddos\ntogether to fill out the student body.
Under any other circumstances, I would\nthink an increase in educational facilities\na good thing...
But this is Emile we're talking about.\nJust what is he scheming THIS time?
That's a saddening lack of trust.\nEntirely substantiated, mind you,\nbut still rather pitiful.
Do we have nothing more to go on? Any\nstated purpose in establishing the schools,\nor what manner of children he's gathering?
About all we know is the main branch's\nlocation. It's actually not far from the New\nAlberian border.
Maybe it has some relation to the recent\nincursions we've been seeing at our own\nborder locations.
You believe they've increased security\nthere, and that's led to more frequent\nattacks on our soil?
It's entirely possible. At any rate, we\nneed more information if we're to act.
First, we should ascertain if the children\nare in danger, and second, whether or not\nthis development poses a threat to us.
Right. We may learn something if we\nwere to pay the main campus a visit.

What, just flit up to the front desk and say
＂One enrollment into St. Jerk's School
of Maximum Sketchiness, please＂?
Not smart, bucko. They know all our faces!
This is to say nothing of the difficulty a\nband of adults would face in infiltrating a\nfacility for children.
A fair point. Hm... There ARE some\nchildren here in the Halidom, but—
It's a dangerous enough mission for adults.\nI won't allow you to send CHILDREN. No.\nAbsolutely not!
Be at ease. I agree with you. I'll not\nsend any children there, least of all\nyour brother, Lowen.
Good. So long as we're in agreement.
So what IS the plan, then?
Let's go in undercover as kids ourselves!
Ranzal. Have... Have you SEEN yourself?\nKindly keep your suggestions to the realm\nof the possible and—
Yes. Though the procedure carries with it\ncertain risks.
Why don't you explain the process to us\nfirst? Then we can make a decision.
It's simple. We explode you all.
Explosion. It's a sudden oxidation process.\nThe one I'm always bothering you all with?
Er, yes, I don't think that was where you\nlost her. What do you mean by ＂explode\nus all,＂ specifically?
Well, you see, a few weeks back...
Oof. There goes another one...\nYou all right, Pipple?
...Pipple? Wait. Am I seeing this right?
You've regressed back to just a sprout!
Fascinating! What underlying mechanism\ncould have caused such a transformation?
I need to start researching this, STAT!
I have...so many questions. First among\nthem being: is poor Pipple all right?
Oh, he's fit as a ficus. After a while, he\nturned back to normal, none the worse\nfor wear.
So what do you all think?\nFancy a visit to the boom room?
Not like we've got any other bright ideas.\nWhy not give 'er a whirl?
I'm with the big guy on this one! Sinoa's\nexplosions are never fatal. Unless you're a\nbuilding, I guess. In which case, good luck.
Besides, we've all undergone special\ntraining. A little kerblooey or two won't\nkill us.
Kids, don't try this at home.
So, who all's getting blown up?
Ah, about that. There's no predicting who'll\nbe affected, so we should all explode\ntogether.
At the risk of repeating myself... I'm sorry?
I was caught up in the blast alongside\nPipple, but he was the only one made\nyounger.
I still haven't fully pinpointed the specific\nconditions that produce the effect.
But with this many people, it should work\non at least some of you. Probably.
As Luca pointed out, though, we have no\ngood alternatives. I say we give it a try.
Lovely. Come to my chamber once\nyou've made peace with your decision,\nand I can brief you on the particulars.
You reckon a sylvan will look any different\nafter getting younger via kablamification?
Now, I understand you all must be uneasy\nabout being blown up, but rest assured, I\nam at least as nervous about it as you all!
Just how is that meant to assure us?!
Lowen... Live strong, even after I'm gone.
Internal mana density has reached the\ntarget value. And next we, er...
Was this it? I think this was it...\nWait, did I have that connected HERE?
You're not inspiring much confidence here,\nSinoa!
*cough* *sputter* Everyone still there?\nLimbs intact and all that good stuff?
Only just. If it'd been anyone but us,\nwe'd be goners for sure.
No kidding. That was a helluva ride.
And so, may I present to you...
Why is it ME? I didn't think it'd be me...
You really are still an adult in there.
Yes, that much was confirmed by Pipple's\ncase.
How were you able to confirm anything\nby talking to someone who can only say\nan assortment of riffs on ＂Pipple＂?
...You know what? Don't answer that. Not\nworth the time to go down that rabbit hole.
So, now that you're...as you are, will you\ngo to this academy, Ranzal? Louise?
I mean, that was kinda the whole\npoint of doin' this.
Excellent. The rest of us will escort you\nthere, fending off any fiends or imperials\nwe encounter along the way.
Just one last word of caution:\ntry to come back as soon as possible.
The effects should last at least a few days,\nbut past that, there's no telling when\nyou'll revert to normal.
It wasn't an issue going from adult to child\nsize, but the reverse has the potential to\ncause quite a scene.
Let's just say you may find yourself\nstanding atop a pile of shredded kidwear\nin, er...all your natural glory.
So please do come back home before you\nput on a show for all the world to see.\nBest of luck. Take care, now.
All right, then let's get the two of you—
Ha ha, can't you tell? It's Mercury.
Mercury... As in, the Waterwyrm?!\nBut why are you here in human form?
Because I thought this sounded like a fine\ntime to teach Emile an overdue lesson.
I would like to accompany you on your\nacademy infiltration, as I am now.
So you went to the trouble of taking on\nhuman guise... But I fear this particular\ntrick is for kids, as it were.
A flyer? Let's see here...\n＂Teachers Wanted＂?
I've been around for quite some time, so\nI have no shortage of curriculum to pull\nfrom. Plus, no one knows me in this form.
I believe I am the right person for the job.
Well, if you're willing to do it, your\nhelp would certainly be appreciated.
My pleasure. Now, come along, children.
I don't expect we'll be able to avoid battle.\nI just hope we can make it there all right...
Hard to say, considering we're chargin'\nright into enemy territory. As kids, even.
We shall deliver you as close to the school\nas we are able. Until then, it's best we\nstick together.
Leave the fiends and imperials to us.\nYou just focus on infiltrating that school.
It's quite the heavy responsibility, I admit.\nBut we'll see it through!
Let our foes reveal themselves before us.\nThey shall be swept away by the current of\nmy purifying waters.
We'll do anything it takes to make it back\nbefore we end up strikin' a pose in our\nbirthday suits!
